rComments: A lot of people don't like her, but she wasn't that bad. It was her first time teaching the course and it's a very very hard course to teach. The school should hire a histologist, ideally, but with her background and all, she did the best she could. I would read the textbook but it's excellent and very interesting  (grade = A+)

Went off on long tangents which you actually had to pay attention to because she tested on what she said. Made mistakes all the time during lecture. You will do well if you're good at memorizing, but half the stuff we learned was probably wrong. Don't read the textbook as she contradicts it often, you'll just get confused. Very rude prof!

Professor with an attitude problem! Stay away! She makes easy material  difficult due to her terrible marking style, extremely inflexible and unhelpful. It was a painful experience taking this course with her. Class avg ~C+

I did not enjoy her course at all. She makes grotesque mistakes during lectures, has an abysmal teaching style, and watching her lectures makes me tear up in pain. She refuses to acknowledge mistakes in marking and will not correct grades. Our TA was amazing however. I love histology, but I would not recommend taking if she is your professor.
